Claralw(-at-)aol.com writes:

>>Time period.  The later splitties had th  colour code, the earlier
the word.  
>>Forget when the change was.  My 61 15 window's tag says SWR/BG

The change was at the end of the 1963 model run in July 1963 with
chassis number 1.144.281.  The 1964 model with the larger rear
hatch/glass, etc. had the six-digit numeric paint code.  The L-Codes
weren't on the metal M-Code plate, but on an adhesive sticker usually
stuck below the metal plate.

-Jim Bryant
